article.headline: Illini hold Banks to nine points
article.linkText: Illinois wins tenth straight at United Center
article.story:
CHICAGO (Ticker) -- Roger Powell and Illinois continue to feel 
at home upstate in the United Center.

Powell scored 17 points as the 19th-ranked Fighting Illini
posted a 75-60 victory over Illinois-Chicago.

Illinois (8-2) won its 10th straight game at the United Center,
including an 84-61 rout of Arkansas on December 3, and improved
to 23-6 overall at the home of the NBA's Chicago Bulls.

James Augustine and Luther Head each chipped in 13 points for
Illinois, which has four straight.  The Illini have won nine
straight against the Flames.

Illinois-Chicago (9-4) lost its second straight on the heels of
a three-game winning streak.  Cedric Banks, the Flames' leading
scorer at 19.6 points, was held to nine.
